  "prompt": "I am doing 3rd integrated MS.c.Life sciences and I am going to apply for INSA summer research fellowship.What the write up should contain generally?",
  "response": "Applying for the INSA Summer Research Fellowship involves submitting a write-up that reflects your research interests, academic background, and motivation for applying. Here\u2019s a general guideline on what to include:\n\n1. **Introduction**:\n   - Briefly introduce yourself, your current academic status, and the institution you are studying at.\n   - Mention the field you are interested in within life sciences and express your enthusiasm for research.\n\n2. **Academic Background**:\n   - Detail your coursework, relevant subjects, and any specific projects or internships you have undertaken.\n   - Highlight any notable accomplishments, awards, or recognitions.\n\n3. **Research Interests**:\n   - Clearly describe your specific areas of interest within life sciences.\n   - Explain why these areas fascinate you and how they align with your long-term career goals.\n   - Include any particular problems or questions within these areas that intrigue you.\n\n4. **Previous Research Experience**:\n   - Provide an overview of any previous research experience, internships, or notable projects.\n   - Explain the methodologies you employed, results obtained, and your contributions to the work.\n   - If you have published papers or presented at conferences, mention them.\n\n5. **Motivation for Applying**:\n   - Articulate why you are applying for the INSA Summer Research Fellowship.\n   - Explain how this fellowship would benefit you academically and professionally.\n   - Mention any specific labs, researchers, or projects within INSA you are particularly interested in.\n\n6. **Future Goals**:\n   - Discuss your long-term career aspirations.\n   - Explain how the fellowship aligns with these goals and how it will help you achieve them.\n   - Mention any plans for further studies or specific research directions you wish to pursue.\n\n7. **Conclusion**:\n   - Summarize your overall candidacy, reiterating your passion for research and how the fellowship will aid your journey.\n   - Thank the committee for considering your application.\n\n**Additional Tips**:\n- Be concise but comprehensive.\n- Ensure clarity and coherence in your write-up.\n- Avoid plagiarism and ensure the write-up is entirely your work.\n- Proofread to eliminate any grammatical or typographical errors.\n\nUltimately, your write-up should reflect your genuine interest in life sciences research and convey a clear and compelling case for why you deserve the fellowship.",
